item.description:
Multiple Button text descriptions do not make sense out of context. For example when tabbing to the &quot;Add/Edit properties&quot; button, it simply says &quot;Properties&quot;
<br/>

<br/>
Original code:
<br/>
&lt;div class=&quot;act&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;Properties&quot; name=&quot;eventSubmit_doProperties&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;/div&gt;
<br/>
&lt;p class=&quot;instruction&quot;&gt;Add/Edit pages&lt;/p&gt;
<br/>
&lt;div class=&quot;act&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;Pages&quot; name=&quot;eventSubmit_doPages&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;/div&gt;
<br/>
&lt;p class=&quot;instruction&quot;&gt;Add/Edit groups&lt;/p&gt;
<br/>
&lt;div class=&quot;act&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;Groups&quot; name=&quot;eventSubmit_doGroups&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;/div&gt;
<br/>

<br/>
Recommended remediation:
<br/>
Use full description of button&#39;s function for text label.
<br/>

<br/>
&lt;div class=&quot;act&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;Add/Edit Properties&quot; name=&quot;eventSubmit_doProperties&quot;&gt; (Add &quot;Add/Edit&quot; to the value attribute)
<br/>
&lt;/div&gt;
<br/>
&lt;p class=&quot;instruction&quot;&gt;Add/Edit pages&lt;/p&gt;
<br/>
&lt;div class=&quot;act&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;Add/Edit Pages&quot; name=&quot;eventSubmit_doPages&quot;&gt; (Add &quot;Add/Edit&quot; to the value attribute)
<br/>
&lt;/div&gt;
<br/>
&lt;p class=&quot;instruction&quot;&gt;Add/Edit groups&lt;/p&gt;
<br/>
&lt;div class=&quot;act&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input type=&quot;submit&quot; value=&quot;Add/Edit Groups&quot; name=&quot;eventSubmit_doGroups&quot;&gt; (Add &quot;Add/Edit&quot; to the value attribute)
<br/>
&lt;/div&gt;

Published, Joinable, Public View, Custom Page Order radio buttons do not have a fieldset or legend. For instance, tabbing to the Joinable No radio button screen reading software announces &quot;No Radio button checked 2 of 2&quot; and does not announce what you are saying no to. 
<br/>

<br/>
Recommended remediation:
<br/>

<br/>
Use fieldsets and legends for the radio buttons. 
<br/>
&lt;fieldset&gt;
<br/>
&lt;legend&gt;Published:&lt;/legend&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input id=&quot;publishedfalse&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;published&quot; value=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;label for=&quot;publishedfalse&quot;&gt; unpublished &lt;/label&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input id=&quot;publishedtrue&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; checked=&quot;checked&quot; name=&quot;published&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;label for=&quot;publishedtrue&quot;&gt; published &lt;/label&gt;
<br/>
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
<br/>
...
<br/>
&lt;fieldset&gt;
<br/>
&lt;legend&gt;Joinable?:&lt;/legend&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input id=&quot;opentrue&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; checked=&quot;checked&quot; name=&quot;joinable&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;label for=&quot;opentrue&quot;&gt; yes &lt;/label&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input id=&quot;openfalse&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;joinable&quot; value=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;label for=&quot;openfalse&quot;&gt; no&lt;/label&gt;
<br/>
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
<br/>
...
<br/>
&lt;fieldset&gt;
<br/>
&lt;legend&gt;Public View?:&lt;/legend&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input id=&quot;pubViewtrue&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; checked=&quot;checked&quot; name=&quot;pubView&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;label for=&quot;pubViewtrue&quot;&gt; yes&lt;/label&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input id=&quot;pubViewfalse&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;pubView&quot; value=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;label for=&quot;pubViewfalse&quot;&gt; no &lt;/label&gt;
<br/>
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
<br/>
...
<br/>
&lt;fieldset&gt;
<br/>
&lt;legend&gt;Custom Page Order?:&lt;/legend&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input id=&quot;customOrdertrue&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; name=&quot;customOrder&quot; value=&quot;true&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;label for=&quot;customOrdertrue&quot;&gt; yes&lt;/label&gt;
<br/>
&lt;input id=&quot;customOrderfalse&quot; type=&quot;radio&quot; checked=&quot;checked&quot; name=&quot;customOrder&quot; value=&quot;false&quot;&gt;
<br/>
&lt;label for=&quot;customOrderfalse&quot;&gt; no &lt;/label&gt;
<br/>
&lt;/fieldset&gt;
<br/>

<br/>
NOTE!: Fieldsets cannot be nested inside tables.  This is not valid HTML code.  The table should be replaced with div elements. Or the fieldsets and legends could be hidden.
<br/>
